TOPIC: LOOPS

WHAT ARE LOOPS?

Loops are used to execute a block of code again and again until a condition is met.

👉 Instead of writing same code multiple times, loops automate repetition.

Example without loop:
console.log("Hello");
console.log("Hello");
console.log("Hello");

Example with loop:
for (let i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
console.log("Hello");
}

WHY WE USE LOOPS?
To avoid repetition
To save time
To make code clean and efficient

Real-life example:
👉 Brushing teeth daily → repeated task
👉 Loop = repeating action automatically

TYPES OF LOOPS IN JAVASCRIPT
for loop
while loop
do-while loop
for-of loop
for-in loop
FOR LOOP

Used when number of iterations is known

Syntax:

for (initialization; condition; update) {
// code
}

Example:

for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
console.log(i);
}

FLOW OF FOR LOOP:

Step 1: initialization → let i = 1
Step 2: condition → i <= 5
Step 3: run code
Step 4: update → i++
Repeat

VISUAL:

i = 1 → print
i = 2 → print
i = 3 → print
i = 4 → print
i = 5 → print
stop

WHILE LOOP

Used when number of iterations is unknown

Syntax:

while (condition) {
// code
}

Example:

let i = 1;

while (i <= 5) {
console.log(i);
i++;
}

FLOW:

Check condition → run → update → repeat

DO-WHILE LOOP

Runs at least once (even if condition is false)

Syntax:

do {
// code
} while (condition);

Example:

let i = 1;

do {
console.log(i);
i++;
} while (i <= 5);

IMPORTANT:

Even if condition is false initially, code runs once

FOR-OF LOOP

Used for iterating over iterable values (strings, arrays)

Syntax:

for (let value of iterable) {
// code
}

Example:

let str = "hello";

for (let char of str) {
console.log(char);
}

Output:
h e l l o

FOR-IN LOOP

Used for iterating over object keys

Syntax:

for (let key in object) {
// code
}

Example:

let student = {
name: "Anant",
age: 20
};

for (let key in student) {
console.log(key, student[key]);
}

INFINITE LOOP

A loop that never ends

Example:

while (true) {
console.log("Infinite");
}

❌ Dangerous → can crash browser/system

BREAK AND CONTINUE

BREAK:
Stops loop completely

Example:

for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
if (i === 3) break;
console.log(i);
}

Output:
1 2

CONTINUE:
Skips current iteration

Example:

for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
if (i === 3) continue;
console.log(i);
}

Output:
1 2 4 5

NESTED LOOPS

Loop inside another loop

Example:

for (let i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
for (let j = 1; j <= 2; j++) {
console.log(i, j);
}
}

REAL-LIFE USE CASES
Printing lists
Processing arrays
Games (loop until correct answer)
Repeating tasks

Example:

Guessing game:

let correct = 5;
let guess;

while (guess !== correct) {
guess = prompt("Enter number");
}

COMMON MISTAKES
Forgetting update (i++) → infinite loop
Wrong condition
Using wrong loop type
Off-by-one errors
